FuncDef: The undo rule command deletes an ACL6 rule in the advanced ACL6 view. The undo rule command deletes an ACL6 rule in the advanced ACL6 view. By default, no advanced ACL6 rule is created.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies a start rule ID for advanced ACL6 rules to be deleted in batches.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967294.

Specifies an end rule ID for advanced ACL6 rules to be deleted in batches.to-rule-id must be no less than rule-id.
The value is an integer ranging from 0 to 4294967294.

ExtraInfo: To delete an ACL rule in the advanced ACL6 view, run the undo rule command.
